    <p><strong>Doctoral Colloquium</strong></p> 
<p>The colloquium functions to introduce graduate students to one another and to FCAD faculty affiliated with the program. Faculty presentations on relevant project research will be broadly contextualized through an interdisciplinary and expansive reading course that surveys the fields of creative media and design. A thematic focus relevant to practice-based research will be provided as a way of demonstrating connections across the program areas of concentration.<img src="/etc.clientlibs/ryecms/static/clientlib-site/resources/images/separators/transparent_separator.png" alt=" " role="presentation" class="hr-separator hr-separator-default"></p> 
<p><strong>Qualitative Research Methods</strong></p> 
<p>This course exposes students to a variety of epistemological approaches. (If warranted by the research project, a student would be allowed to take a Quantitative Research Methods course in place of the Qualitative Research Methods course pending availability within the university.)</p>
    





